p2
VVenumadhav&#8217;s pleasing recital
p3
sVnews
p4
VSattiraju Venumadhav performed at the Thyagaraya Ganasabha, last week denoting all the compositions he rendered were in devotion to Srirama called &#8216;Ramabhakti Samrajyam&#8217;.He was accompanied by Kolanka Saikumar on violin, T. P. Balasubramanyam on mridagam and Gunaranjan on Kanjira.A gifted vocalist Venumadhav carried the day well with his melodious and resonant voice. He was conscious of thesahityabhavain all the numbers he rendered. He gave a traditional opening to his concert withViriboni,Bhairavi ata tala varnamand followed it with Thyagaraja&#8217;s Nata compositionNinne Bhajana.His pleasant style of kirtana rendition was particularly witnessed in the rendition ofSitamma Mayammain Vasantha andRamabhakti Samrajyamin Suddha Bangala, both of Thyagaraja, before he took up the first raga essay of the concert, Hindolam.He presented it neatly and sang Annamacharya&#8217;sDevadevam BhajeinKhandachapu talam. Theswarashe wove in this were interesting.Sarasasamadanain Kapinarayani was a quickie and the followingNagumomuin Abheri was a delightful rendition.After rendering another brief numberBantureetiinHamsanadamhe choseKharaharapriyaas his main raga of the concert.He delineated it well, building tempo as it progressed into higher octaves.Rama Neesamanamevaruwas his choice kriti in this in Roopaka talam. Besides the pleasant rendition of this composition, thenerevalhe presented at the linePaluku Palukuku Teniyalolukunatulawas interesting. The swarprasthara that followed spoke again of his command on the grammar. The concluding numbers included a Ramadasu kirtna -Yeteeruga nanuin Nadanamakriya. On this occasion, an audio CD of Venumadhav&#8217;s songs and a book of compilation of 506 kirtanas of Annamayya with the tile Annamayya Sankeertana Ratnakaramu were released by noted poet and Sahasravadhani Dr. Garikapati Narasimha Rao.
